cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the vulnerability of malware detection methods to evasion attacks. It also involves the use of machine learning and deep neural networks, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it deals with the detection of malicious software in executable files. Finally, the use of gradient-based attacks could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
